x4freetext: -NEUTRON CAPTURE MEASUREMENTS IN THE RESONANCE REGION,
.SAMPLES OF NATURAL COPPER WITH THICKNESSES OF
DATA FROM SAMPLE OF THICKNESS 0.0337 ATOMS/B
TIME OF FLIGHT, 30 AND 60 METER FLIGHT
PATHS, NOMINAL RESOLUTION BETWEEN 3.5 AND 1 NSEC/M
MODIFIED MOXON RAE DETECTOR, WITH 6 EQUALLY
COINCIDENCE. THE EFFICIENCY IS SHOWN TO BE LINEARLY
DEPENDANT ON GAMMA ENERGY IN NIM,50,265,67.
KNOWN PARAMETERS OF RESONANCES IN AG AT 5.2, 16.3 AND
51.4 EV AND THE 20.46 EV RESONANCE IN PU-240.
.QUOTED ERRORS ON RESONANCE PARAMETERS CONTIAN BOTH
EXPERIMENTAL UNCERTAINTIES, MAINLY DUE TO ABSOLUTE
FLUX CALIBRATION, AND UNCERTAINTY IN ASSUMED
AREA ANALYSIS WITH GACA PROGRAM OF FROEHNER
AND SPIN TAKEN FROM BNL-235,VOL 2, ED 2.
